1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
PROJECT B is a social-mobility intelligence platform that solves one universal human problem: “Where should we meet?”
Unlike navigation apps built for individuals, PROJECT B is engineered for group equity. It eliminates the invisible labor of organizing friends by algorithmically finding the optimal meeting point based on every participant’s location, budget elasticity, and transport mode — then lets the group vote and book in one continuous flow.
Core Promise: Equity in distance. Simplicity in decision.
Tagline Ecosystem: - “Where B. is your journey starts” - “Weekend at B’s” - “Join B” - “B. knows where.”
The Problem: Organizing group meetups creates emotional labor, social friction, and geographic unfairness. Someone always travels farther. Someone always pays more. Someone (usually the same person) does all the planning.
The Solution: B. — a friendly algorithmic concierge that makes fairness automatic, visible, and effortless.
