6.2 The Equity Engine (Core Algorithm)
Instead of finding the geographic midpoint, PROJECT B calculates the “Burden Index” for each participant:
Burden(i) = (Time(i) × TimeWeight(i)) + (Money(i) × MoneyWeight(i))
Optimization Target: Minimize the maximum burden across all participants (minimax fairness).
Group Filters: - Time Priority: “Nobody travels more than X minutes” - Money Priority: “Total group transport cost under €Y” - Hybrid Mode: Individual sliders — “I’m willing to spend more to save time” vs. “I’m broke but have time”
6.3 Decision Layer
1.	Heatmap View: Overlapping accessibility zones with intensity = equity quality
2.	Venue Suggestions: Restaurants, bars, hotels, activities within the equitable zone
3.	Group Vote: Swipe-style voting for final venue (Tinder-style yes/no)
4.	Itinerary Export: Per-person route links, calendar invites, split-bill setup
