7. THE EQUITY ENGINE
7.1 Mathematical Foundation
Input: - Set of participants P = {p₁, p₂, …, pₙ} - For each pᵢ: origin coordinates (latᵢ, lonᵢ) - For each pᵢ: transport mode mᵢ ∈ {walk, bike, transit, car, train, flight} - For each pᵢ: time weight wₜᵢ ∈ [0, 1] - For each pᵢ: money weight wₘᵢ ∈ [0, 1] - For each pᵢ: max time budget Tᵢ - For each pᵢ: max money budget Mᵢ
Output: - Optimal meeting zone Z* that minimizes max(Burden(pᵢ)) for all pᵢ ∈ P - Alternative zones Z₁, Z₂, Z₃ ranked by equity score
Algorithm: 1. Generate candidate zones using spatial grid + POI density 2. For each candidate zone z: a. Calculate route from each pᵢ to z for mode mᵢ b. Extract time tᵢ and cost cᵢ c. Calculate Burden(pᵢ) = (tᵢ × wₜᵢ) + (cᵢ × wₘᵢ) d. Record max_burden(z) = max(Burden(pᵢ)) e. Record equity_score(z) = 1 - (std_dev(Burden) / mean(Burden)) 3. Filter zones where Burden(pᵢ) ≤ Tᵢ and cᵢ ≤ Mᵢ for all pᵢ 4. Rank by: 0.7 × equity_score + 0.3 × (1 / max_burden) 5. Return top 3 zones with full burden breakdown
7.2 Equity Visualization
The map uses concentric accessibility bubbles rather than pins: - Green overlap: High equity (all participants have similar burden) - Yellow overlap: Acceptable equity (some variation, within thresholds) - Red zones: Vetoed (exceeds someone’s hard constraints)
B. drops the pin in the deepest green zone with a celebratory animation.
